sketch.compiler.codegenerators.tojava

Class StmtIODecl

  • java.lang.Object
    • sketch.compiler.ast.core.FENode
      • sketch.compiler.ast.core.stmts.Statement
        • sketch.compiler.codegenerators.tojava.StmtIODecl

  • public class StmtIODecl
extends Statement
    An old-syntax I/O rate declaration. This has a name, a type, and one or two integer rates. It gets translated to a statement like 
     name = new Channel(type.class, rate1, rate2);
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    David Maze <dmaze@cag.lcs.mit.edu>

    • Constructor Detail

      • StmtIODecl

        public StmtIODecl(FENode context,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  Type type,
                  Expression rate1,
                  Expression rate2)
        Creates a new I/O rate declaration. The name should be either "input" or "output". If it is "output", rate1 is the push rate. If the name is "input", rate1 is the pop rate, and rate2 is the peek rate. The second rate can be null if it is unnecessary or it is equal to the first rate.
        Parameters:
        context - Context this statement appears in
        name - Name of the channel
        type - Type of objects on this channel
        rate1 - Push or pop rate
        rate2 - Peek rate or null

      • getRate2

        public Expression getRate2()
        Returns the peek rate of the stream. Returns null if this is an output channel or if the peek rate is undeclared and implicitly equal to the pop rate.
